title: Trump loyalists say charges are 'Democrat ploy' as polls show no opening for DeSantis
description: Donald Trump was the frontrunner to be the Republican Party nominee for the 2024 presidential race before news of his pending arrest became public - and that fact is unchanged even now he is officially a criminal defendant.

title: Ukraine needs the public on its side - but that isn't a problem in Poland
description: From the start, Volodymyr Zelenskyy's first official visit to Poland since Russia invaded Ukraine was a meeting of friends.

title: Taiwan faces 'unprecedented challenges' as US welcomes president despite China's warnings
description: Taiwan's peace and democracy are facing "unprecedented challenges", its president has said, on a visit to the US which will anger China.

title: Man jailed for kidnapping four-year-old girl in Australia
description: A man who kidnapped a four-year-old girl and held her captive for 18 days has been sentenced to more than 13 years in prison.

title: Tornado kills 'multiple' people in Missouri
description: A tornado has caused "multiple injuries and multiple deaths" in Missouri, US officials have said.

title: Four children killed after man wielding hatchet attacks nursery in Brazil
description: A man armed with a hatchet has killed four children after he attacked a nursery in Brazil.

title: Spanish actress, 68, reveals surrogate baby is her late son's
description: A 68-year-old Spanish actress has revealed how she used her son's DNA to create a surrogate baby - to fulfil his dying wish to have a child.

title: Monopoly game 'ends in samurai swordfight' with man said to be fighting for his life
description: A samurai swordfight broke out in Brussels when a game of Monopoly went wrong, according to reports.

title: Biden to visit Northern Ireland and the Republic next week
description: US President Joe Biden will visit Northern Ireland and the Republic next week, the White House has announced.

title: Jacinda Ardern gets standing ovation as she delivers farewell speech to New Zealand parliament
description: Jacinda Ardern was given a standing ovation as she delivered her farewell speech to the New Zealand parliament.

title: Cruise passenger dies after falling from ship balcony and hitting person below
description: A passenger on a Virgin Voyages cruise has died after falling off their balcony shortly after the ship set off.

title: Israeli riot police fire stun grenades and tear gas in clashes with Palestinian worshippers
description: Israeli riot police have fired stun grenades and tear gas inside al Aqsa Mosque in clashes with Palestinian worshippers in the early hours of Wednesday morning.

title: Donald Trump claims he's a victim of 'election interference' in first speech since being charged in New York
description: Donald Trump has claimed he is the victim of election interference, as he condemned New York District Attorney Alvin Bragg for bringing criminal charges against him - speaking just hours after his arraignment.
